<td style=3D"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #010101; fon=
t-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;" align=3D"left">
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style19" align=3D"justify">The s=
uccess or failure of a product in the market is determined much before its =
actual launch and is enabled by an effective New Product Development (NPD) =
Process. Dovetailing the market strategy and the product and technology roa=
d-maps with the overall business strategy is critical for the firm to be co=
mpetitive.&nbsp;&nbsp; Market research and tools like VPH help in listening=
 to the voice of the customer and gaining insights into what is perceived a=
s value for money.&nbsp; Structured requirements development techniques hel=
p capture and translate the right product requirements into technical speci=
fications. NPD involves an interdisciplinary approach and effective cross-f=
unctional teaming. Robust portfolio management is a must for evaluating and=
 selecting the appropriate NPD projects addressing the product requirements=
. It also mandates a structured approach to planning, development gates dur=
ing execution including Go/No Go decision points and pro-active risk manage=
ment. Technical activities are enabled by tools like DFMEA and Dfx. Last bu=
t not least, activities during product testing and post market introduction=
 like field monitoring help address teething problems, including customer p=
erception management.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style19" align=3D"justify"><span=
 style=3D"color: #0000ff;" class=3D"style29">Keeping this in view, <strong>=
T&Uuml;V Rheinland Academy and Life Care </strong> is organising a <strong>=
2 days training program on New Product Development Process on 25th & 26th F=
eb&#39;16 at Delhi/NCR.</strong></span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style19"><span class=3D"style30"=
><strong>Benefits</strong>: <br /> Aligning the NPD process to fit into the=
 larger context of the organizational strategy and business needs is a key =
take away.&nbsp; Seamlessly anticipating and addressing execution issues wi=
th the involved stakeholders, in line with the product road-map is another =
learning. Key points to ensure harnessing the support from Senior Executive=
 Team and effectively liaisoning with the functional teams would be discuss=
ed.</span></p>
<p class=3D"style19"><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em><strong>Key focus =
areas of the workshop:</strong></em></span></p>
<ul class=3D"style19">
<li><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em>Strategic Perspective and cross fun=
ctional interfaces for NPD</em></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em>Portfolio Management of NPD project=
s</em></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em>Measures of NPD success</em></span>=
</li>
<li><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em>Key Phases in Product Realization</=
em></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em>Proactive Risk Management (Project =
and Product)</em></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em>Overview of Key Tools that enable N=
PD</em></span>
<blockquote>
<p><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em>- Market Research </em></span><br />=
<span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em> - VOC/VPH</em></span><br /><span style=
=3D"color: #800000;"><em> - DfX </em></span><br /><span style=3D"color: #80=
0000;"><em> - DFMEA</em></span><br /><span style=3D"color: #800000;"><em> -=
 Product Launch Evaluation & Field Monitoring</em></span></p>
</blockquote>
</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"style19"><strong>Methodology of the training programme</strong>=
:</p>
<ul class=3D"style19">
<li>Case studies</li>
<li>Examples</li>
<li>Scenarios</li>
<li>And other accelerated learning activities are included to ensure a &ldq=
uo;hands on&rdquo; training session</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style19" align=3D"justify"><stro=
ng>Recommended Participants for effectiveness:</strong> <br /> Business Lea=
ders, Business Managers, Program Managers, Product Managers, Project Manage=
rs, Marketing Managers, Quality and R&D professionals who desire to enable =
their organizational journey towards successful NPD and robust product real=
ization practices in order to ensure a competitive edge enabling their busi=
ness growth.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style19" align=3D"justify"><stro=
ng>Faculty: </strong>Highly experienced faculty from <strong>TUV Rheinland =
Academy and Life Care </strong>will conduct this training. it will provide =
participants an opportunity to discuss specific problems with the expert fa=
culty.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;"><span class=3D"style19"><span class=3D"st=
yle31"><strong>Registration Fee:</strong> Rs.10,000/- per participant (14% =
of service tax extra) which includes Cost of certificate, Course material, =
Lunch & Coffee/Tea etc. </span></span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style32"><strong>Early bird offe=
r:</strong> 10% discount on delegate fee, if registered with payment on or =
before 17th Feb 2016.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style32"><strong><span style=3D"=
text-decoration: underline;">Group Discount</span>: 10% discount on 3 or mo=
re people from single organization</strong>.</p>
<p class=3D"style33">This is a non-residential course and delegates are req=
uested to make their own arrangements for accommodation.</p>
<p class=3D"style19" align=3D"justify"><strong>This includes comprehensive =
course material, lunch & Coffee/Tea. Registrations will be accepted on &#39=
;First come First Served&#39; basis. Companies interested in participation =
